# Project rules (nav only)

**Always-on sources**

1. [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) — stack, commands, safety, tenant, DB, checks, token discipline
2. [`analysis-before-code.mdc`](./analysis-before-code.mdc) — hard gates; full flow in skill below
3. [`no-polling-except-fallback.mdc`](./no-polling-except-fallback.mdc) — no API polling except realtime fallback
4. [`git-local-merge-push.mdc`](./git-local-merge-push.mdc) — local branch → merge → push; no auto PR / agent merge-main

**Skills (read when task matches `description`)**

- `.cursor/skills/mesa-analyze-before-code/SKILL.md` — analyze-first, end-state, reuse, one-representation gate
- `.cursor/skills/mesa-local-product-test/SKILL.md` — localhost product verification

**On-demand rules** (not alwaysApply): `push-verification.mdc`, `release-and-ci.mdc`, `local-product-testing.mdc` (incl. no checklist skip unless truly blocked) — when push/ship/test phrases appear.

No third root “强制规则” markdown. Product truth under `docs/`.

## Documentation map

| Need | Path |
|------|------|
| Product overview | `docs/product/01-product-overview.md` |
| Feature boundaries | `docs/product/02-feature-map.md` |
| User flows & rules | `docs/product/03-user-flows.md`, `04-business-rules.md` |
| UI conventions | `docs/design/` |
| Architecture & API | `docs/technical/` |
| ADRs | `docs/decisions/` |
| DB compact schema | `docs/ai-schema.md` |
| Historical plans | `docs/*-plan.md`, `docs/*.zh.md` |
| Cleanup phases | `docs/optimization.md` (one phase at a time; confirm before next) |

Before non-trivial edits: read matching rows only — not a whole-repo scan. Prefer `docs/ai-schema.md` over browsing all migrations.

## Mandatory workflow

1. **Read** related docs and targeted code only (default 3–5 files; see `AGENTS.md`)
2. **Plan** — non-trivial logic: follow analysis gates + `mesa-analyze-before-code` skill
3. **Scope** — no out-of-scope features, unrelated files, silent rewrites, or temporary patches
4. **Sync docs** — business rules → `docs/product/` or `docs/technical/`; major tech → `docs/decisions/`
5. **Verify** — checks per `AGENTS.md`; product UAT via `mesa-local-product-test` when asked

## High-risk (explicit user approval)

Checkout/payment, bill splits, table session lifecycle, print jobs & RLS, migrations, order/kitchen void flows.

Do not expose table UUIDs on receipts — use `display_name` only.
